                "a": "Introduction -- The information society and Brazil: opportunities and risks -- Making services available to all citizens (universalisation) -- The information society programme in Brazil -- The evolution of iniciatives towards an information society in the world -- Monitoring indicators -- Computer technology and telecommunications in Brazil -- The internet."
            }
        ],
        "520": {
            "a": "The present volume - The Information Society in Brazil: excerpts from the Green Book - outlines some of the opportunities and challenges presented by the information society as we in Brazil see them: opportunities in the business sector; in the improved efficiency of public services at all levels; in the creating of worthwhile employment; in the fostering of science and technology. Challenges must be faced in terms of the need to: develop an appropriate knowledge based infrastructure; review legal and regulatory systems; and above all; ensure that access to the new technologies such as the internet do not remain the privilege of the few but become, through training, education and efforts by the government and the private sector the universally accessible right of all our citizens, both rich and poor. In this way no-one will be marginalized from this great international adventure marking the beginning of the New Millennium. Ambassador Ronaldo Mota Sardenberg Minister of State for Science and Technology."
        },
